Arsenal stars Mikel Arteta, Santi Cazorla, Bacary Sagna, Tomas Rosicky, Mathieu Flamini and Olivier Giroud will be all hoping their new Puma boots help end the club's nine-year trophy drought when they face Hull in the FA Cup final on Saturday.

The Gunners' contingent debuted their latest footwear, named Tricks, during training ahead of the Wembley showpiece on Wednesday.

